{"word":"ἐμβριθής","slug":"ἐμβριθής","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἐμβριθής</b></el> <el>(ἐμβρῑθής, ές) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><el>ἐν, βρίθω</el>\n<p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>weighty</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><a href='S:metaphorically'>metaph.</a>, like <a href='S:Latin'>Lat.</a> <el>gravis, weighty, grave, dignified</el>, <b><a href='S:Plutarch'>Plut.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>3. </b>in bad sense, <i>heavy, grievous</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}